title: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content:
You should update your UK Visas and Immigration (UKVI) account if you’ve changed your:

  • mobile phone number
  • email address
  • name
  • identity document, such as your passport or national identity card
  • home address
  • postal address

You can also:

  • correct your date of birth
  • add an extra nationality - if you have dual nationality, for example
  • add an extra identity document
  • change your photo, for example if your appearance has changed and you can no longer be recognised from your photo
  • give someone else access to your visa applications, if you’d like them to help you apply
  • give someone else ownership of the UKVI account, if you set up the account on their behalf

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content: You cannot change your identity document or name if you’re waiting for a decision on a visa application.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content:
You’ll have a UK Visas and Immigration account if you’ve ever:

  • applied to the EU Settlement Scheme
  • used the ‘UK Immigration: ID Check’ app to prove your identity when applying for a visa
  • created one when applying for a visa (you’ll have received a UKVI account confirmation email)

Who has a UKVI account
You’ll have a UK Visas and Immigration account if you’ve ever:

  applied to the EU Settlement Scheme
  used the ‘UK Immigration: ID Check’ app to prove your identity when applying for a visa
  created one when applying for a visa (you’ll have received a UKVI account confirmation email)

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content: There’s a different way to update your details if you do not have a UKVI account.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
Why your details need to be up to date
chunks.html_content:
Your details must be up to date so that you can:

  • view and prove your rights to others, for example employers or landlords
  • be contacted by UKVI, for example if you’re waiting for a decision or to have documents returned
  • travel with your current identity document

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content: Sign into your UKVI account to update your details.
chunks.plain_content:
Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
Update your UKVI account details
Sign into your UKVI account to update your details.

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content:
To sign in and update your UK Visas and Immigration (UKVI) account, you’ll need:

  • your identity document - your passport, national identity card, or biometric residence card or permit
  • access to your phone or email address - you’ll get a security code to confirm your identity

To sign in, use the identity document and contact details you gave when you applied, unless you have already used this service to update them.

If you’re updating your name, date of birth or nationality, you’ll also need an identity document that proves the change is needed.

  access to your phone or email address - you’ll get a security code to confirm your identity

To sign in, use the identity document and contact details you gave when you applied, unless you have already used this service to update them.
If you’re updating your name, date of birth or nationality, you’ll also need an identity document that proves the change is needed.

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
chunks.html_content: You cannot use this service to update a UKVI account if you’re registered in the account as a ‘helper’. Only the person who applied can make changes.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Update your UK Visas and Immigration account details
After you’ve updated your UKVI account
chunks.html_content:
This service will only update the details in your UKVI account, not things like a biometric residence permit or a citizenship application, for example.

You’ll be told what else you need to do after you update your UKVI account.
